Basic description: Takes you back to the &quot;safe spot&quot; in the zone, typically at the zoneline, but not always.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1627&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: Prior to the advent of Lesser Evacuate, this was useful for travel -- cast it when in the tunnels leading from the Dreadlands to Firiona Vie to appear right beside the bridge into town, for instance -- but now, with Lesser Evacuate so long a part of the spell line-up (and a cheap and easy to use player-made item with the same effect also available), this is somewhat obsolete. There still will be times where you don't want to drop your group while going to the zoneline, such as when going to the zoneline to invite someone to have Call of the Hero cast on them to bring them to a raid.<br>
Spell era: Ruins of Kunark<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: This spell cannot be researched.<br>
Quest information: <br>
Fironia Vie, Barnal Flamehand<br>
The Overthere, Utandar Rizndown<br>
Drop information: This spell is not dropped by any known NPC.<br>
<br>
Firetree's Familiar Augment<br>
Basic description: Boosts the health, armor and speed of your familiar.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=2556&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: With the ability to do &quot;/pet get lost&quot; and retain all the benefits of having your familiar cast, this all but drops right off the list of useful spells.<br>
Spell era: Shadows of Luclin<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: This spell cannot be researched.<br>
Quest information: This spell is not a quest reward in any known quests.<br>
Drop information: Various NPCs in Fungus Grove.<br>
<br>
Frozen Harpoon<br>
Basic description: You spear an opponent with a harpoon of solid ice.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3706&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: I know, I know, this spell is a puzzler at first glance. Its damage is nice, but not extraordinary, the same with its cast time (and look at that long recast time!). Now look at its mana cost: Along with Ice Spear of Solist and Strike of Solusek, this is one of the most mana efficient direct damage spells in the game. Frozen Harpoon barely sips mana, and coupled with a draught, it serves to extend a mana pool while still doing appreciable damage. Even at my level, I still use this one periodically. <br>
Spell era: Legacy of Ykesha<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: This spell cannot be researched.<br>
Quest information: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.arcanist.com/modules.php?name=Content&pa=showpage&pid=28">www.arcanist.com/modules....age&pid=28</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Drop information: This spell is not dropped by any known NPC.<br>
<br>
Lure of Frost<br>
Basic description: This spell releases a difficult to resist blast of frost, striking a single target.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1642&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Graffë's notes: Lure spells are a great addition to our arsenal in that they allow us to hit mobs that would normally resist everything we threw at them, such as Spite Golems in Hate. They may not hit with as much damage and efficiency as we are accustomed to, but at least we can be a strong part to any group.<br>
Whizbang's notes: Our first &quot;real&quot; lure, this spell will let you damage many things that others simply call &quot;immune.&quot; (Remember to try from in melee range if things still are resisting you.) The lousy mana to damage ratio on these spells means that you should probably just save them for appropriate occasions, however.<br>
Spell era: Ruins of Kunark<br>
Vendor information: <br>
Firiona Vie, Selien Nartoise<br>
The Overthere, Tyrin F'Linz<br>
The Plane of Knowledge, Myrist, Channeler Olaemos<br>
Research information: This spell cannot be researched.<br>
Quest information: This spell is not a quest reward in any known quests.<br>
Drop information: This spell is not dropped by any known NPC.<br>
<br>
Manaskin<br>
Basic description: Creates a damage-absorbing protective force field around you.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1609&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: Now is the time to upgrade from Steelskin. Not only is the upgrade in protection worth it, but this spell also gives an extra point of mana regeneration. Think of it as a Flowing Thought I item in scroll form. The peridot cost will add up over time, however, so only use this as needed.<br>
Spell era: Ruins of Kunark<br>
Vendor information: <br>
Firiona Vie, Selien Nartoise<br>
The Overthere, Tyrin F'Linz<br>
The Plane of Knowledge, Myrist, Channeler Olaemos<br>
Research information: This spell cannot be researched.<br>
Quest information: This spell is not a quest reward in any known quests.<br>
Drop information: This spell is not dropped by any known NPC.<br>
<br>
Tears of Druzzil<br>
Basic description: An area of effect rain spell that does its damage on up to three targets in multiple waves of damage.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1649&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Whizbang's notes: Our first really good rain spell. I find this spell worked exceptionally well, surprisingly so, in the Kael Drakkel arena. Once a melee has sufficiently gained the attention of an opponent, let loose with one of these -- and you can do so earlier than you could fire off a direct damage spell, which is nice -- and while the waves hit, you have time to fire off a draught or two, as you like. Even more powerful when twisted with later tears spells. Note that this spell is also used as a turn-in for the Kunark wizard spell trade-in quests.<br>
Spell era: Ruins of Kunark<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: Sorcerer's Lexicon, Quill, Parchment, Rune of Alternation, Rune of Vortex<br>
Quest information: This spell is not a quest reward in any known quests.<br>
Drop information: Various Kunark NPCs.<br>
<br>
Translocate Group<br>
Basic description: Send your group, individually, to their bind points.<br>
Raw data: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1334&source=Live">lucy.fnord.net/spell.html...ource=Live</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
Graffë's notes: This will send your entire group, excluding yourself, to their bind point. Great when used for parting ways after a day of dungeon crawling.<br>
Whizbang's notes: This used to be a hard sell for me in groups, but the opening of the Nexus and the Plane of Knowledge means that almost everyone seems to be bound in one of those two places, making their bind point convenient to almost everywhere anyway.<br>
Spell era: Scars of Velious<br>
Vendor information: This spell is not sold by any known NPC.<br>
Research information: Sorcerer's Lexicon, Quill, Parchment, Rune of Incendiary, Rune of Transpose<br>
Quest information: This spell is not a quest reward in any known quests.<br>
